The bat has been sent to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention for tests. CAPE TOWN - Two people have been advised to seek post-exposure rabies treatment after a consumer in Florida reported finding a dead bat in a packaged salad mix.The bat has been sent to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) for tests.The CDC says the risk of rabies transmission is extremely low but as a precaution, the two people who ate the salad have been recommended for treatment.